modules.description: Provides operations for arithmetic in finite fields, including addition, multiplication, inversion, and random element generation. Works with elements represented as arbitrary-precision integers under a prime modulus. Used to create JavaScript-compatible finite field implementations for cryptographic or mathematical applications.

This module provides arithmetic operations—addition, multiplication, inversion, exponentiation, and division—alongside checks for field element properties and byte representations, tailored for prime fields. It supports specialized manipulations of roots of unity and quadratic residues, along with encoding/decoding between numeric and byte/string formats, enabling applications in cryptographic protocols and polynomial arithmetic. The type `t` represents field elements, facilitating efficient computations in contexts requiring finite field structures.
